Hey, what a great night last night. Went to practice about 5:15. Started learning a new song which took up most of our time...a Stereophonics song...I forget the name but great song. The fellas walked me through the notations since I never heard the song. I think they were happy with my performance. 

Afterwards we went to the Moore Theater to see Stereophonics....funny ay. Anyway we got there a little late and they had already started, but what great fun. We went all the way up by the stage. That was the closest I had ever been to a band of significance. Depeche Mode comes in second to that. Anyway after the show we went back out to the lobby area and noticed little posters all over, so we each took one down as a souvenier, then we noticed that they were going to sign CD's at 9...so Carlos got a CD and we all got in line and got to meet the band and they signed our little posters and post cards and CD's, what great guys, they were so nice. Afterwards we went next door to the Nitelife and had drinks, smoked cloves and talked music...what a great night. I had the best time.....

Ok, so writing in a journal is something I've done since the age of 12? Not consistently, but on occasion events may happen that I feel I should write about, only because I don't want to forget them. I have a tendency to forget sometimes, which I hate. I wish I could retain information. I've always had a problem with that, maybe that's why I started a journal in the first place. Anyway....this will be interesting, interesting, interesting.

Thanks Ally for the inspiration, although lets see how much I actually use this. It may be a great place to write some melodies....who knows. 

Here's a little something from my brain while sitting on the bus on the way to work one morning:

In the sense of sounding humdrum
